    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-28T22:42:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-28T22:42:00-05:00" n="256"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                <head>256. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Guatemala</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d256fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 175, Folder 1. Unclassified; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Guatemala City</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1954-06-28T21:42:00-06:00">June 28, 1954, 9:42 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>1133. Pass Defense. <persName corresp="#p_DCCE1">Diaz</persName> at 11:45 this
                    morning June 28 issued following Decree establishing Junta consisting of himself
                    and Colonels <persName>Jose Angel Sanchez</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MCE1">Elfego Monzon</persName>.</p>
                <p>“Considering that it is desirable for stability of situation brought about by
                    resignation of Colonel <persName corresp="#p_AGJ1">Jacobo Arbenz
                        Guzman</persName> from position of constitutional president of republic<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d256fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_AGJ1">Arbenz</persName> relinquished the presidency to
                        Army Chief of Staff <persName corresp="#p_DCCE1">Colonel Díaz</persName>
                        June 27.</note> to give to new government broader composition which will
                    lead to representation of other forces and that for these reasons it is
                    convenient to bring into executive Colonels <persName>Jose Angel
                        Sanchez</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MCE1">Elfego Monzon</persName>.
                    Therefore, decrees: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>A governmental Junta be constituted for conducting administration of
                            nation.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Governmental Junta be constituted as follows: <persName
                                corresp="#p_DCCE1">Colonel Carlos Enrique Diaz</persName>, who will
                            serve as chief of armed forces; Colonel <persName>Jose Angel
                                Sanchez</persName>, who will serve as delegate of Junta in Ministry
                            of National Defense; and <persName corresp="#p_MCE1">Colonel Elfego
                                Monzon</persName> who will be delegate of Junta in Ministry of
                            Interior.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>This decree enters into effect day of its publication in <hi
                                rend="italic">Official Gazette</hi>.“<note n="3" xml:id="d256fn3"
                                >The first act of the new junta was to declare the Communist Party
                                illegal. (Telegram 1134 from Guatemala City, June 28; 9:40 p.m.;
                                ibid.)</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PJE1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Peurifoy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
